caption: "0 stars" Horrible Service!!!!! No one there can give us a clear answer or even get back to you. Our wedding was set for May 2, 2020 COVID hit and we had to reschedule our wedding to May 1, 2021. Due to Chicago restriction we are unable to have our wedding so we had to cancel our wedding celebration at Pazzo's and they have yet to refund us over $10,000. Fey stated that the owners are not refunding anything at this moment and its been over a month. After a month finally Pazzo's manager called me back and asked me to call Pazzo's Attorney and there Attorney let me know that Pazzo's will not be refunding us the $10,000 because Pazzo's applied it as an "deposit" I explained that the deposit was $2,500 and that was not included in the $10,000 that we were paying towards our wedding. There Attorney also said that will be not be refunding us the $10,000 unless they find another couple to take our wedding date.?????  Wedding venue worst nightmare. Someone please help us!!!
Great place to grab a quick bite! Fries are always crispy, the Buffalo wraps are awesome and the prices are just right
This spot never fails to deliver. They have excellent food for fair pricing, there is no waiting time even when they are loaded.
Great clean restaurant with great food

This restaurant is my favorite. I visit plenty of restaurants but here I go the most. The stuff is very attentive and the cooking they place on your table is so delicious. I never decline to have a decent meal here. I highly recommend this place.

The service was great the issue was the noodles were tucked together and when you paid $18 dollars for a plate and only two tables at 5 pm doing rush hour spend a little time make it correct, great customer service beautiful atmosphere been a while since I’ve visited Chicago I’m sorry have to said not happy with food,

We went there for a vendor sponsored work lunch. This was my first time there. It was very nice. The place was classy, the service was excellent, and the food was very good. I ordered linguine with scallops. Our cameras in a alfredo type sauce, but not as heavy. The scallops were not over cooked and neither was the pasta. Being at work no one ordered alcohol, but whatever other drink were had they kept our glasses full. The food so abundant that no one had room for dessert. the prices were right too. Definitely going back.

Had the Chicken with garlic wine sauce,  great taste. Very nice and cozy, since they have an indoor terrace I suggest going there during the day, the atmosphere is very nice when the sun beams through the large windows.  Marble everywhere in terrace,  very nice. Christmas decoration was done very elegantly

The service was good. Place was beautiful. Food tasted alright, it's just that it wasn't what it supposed to be! My chicken piccata didn't have enough sauce, had no flavor of lemon, no capers at all, and was topped with fresh chopped tomatos. I almost thought it was the wrong order. Upon inquiring about the absence of capers, server responded that they would have added the capers, if I'd requested. Amusing response!
I like the jambalaya rice there.

For this event, food was great, service was great, the space is great. It's beautiful and airy. Only drawback is understanding a speaker due to that space not being created for that acoustically. The music was just fine, though. Def consider for ~150 ppl; more is a bit crowded.
Good old Irish wedding
Cool spot
Great service!
Very visually nice place. However, the way the tables were set up, it was very difficult to hear the speeches.

Quite a few visits back again. The service is good, the value is very good and most of the food is great. The calamari is a little chewy. The pasta dishes are usually great. I love the Mediterranean penne. Associated had the chicken piccata and the chicken parmesan and loved them both. The atrium setting is very nice. Worth a visit.

The chicken parm with pasta was amazing. I had zero complaints nor did my two friends. The chicken was tender, large portioned, with delicious mozzarella cheese melted on top. The sauce was perfect and the food was served pipping hot just how I like it. Oh and I was SHOCKED when our food came out sooo fast (about 10 mins or less). We were there at an off time though since we were trying to make a 7pm appointment elsewhere. I think we ate around 5pm which is pretty early for a Friday. The atmosphere in the atrium was great. There were palm trees and I think some sort of water feature too. There is also indoor dinning as well but both areas are air-conditioned. We'll definitely return!
Always had good food and service here at a fair price. Service was good as it always is. Love having the option of dining'inside' or in the atrium.
Very tasty and nice location 👌
Very good food, good service. Nice place for a quiet lunch downtown.
Good restaurant! I recommend. But just if you want to eat something correct. It’s not a great Italian, too much garlic on majority of the plate

Lovely resturant with beautiful decor. The attention to detail is superb. The staff is friendly and have perfect timing.  All the menu items are surprisingly reasonably priced as well. Just a hint of advice, skip the garlic and olive oil pasta if you’re networking. Although it tasted good, it was poignant. Truthfully, I was nervous when the plate was sat before me because the aroma was amazing and I knew then, I was in big trouble 🤣
Went here for a wedding, absolutely beautiful.

Linguine w/clams, shrimp, scallops...#thatsAmore'...a quaint but elegant lunchtime gem in the loop that will give you yo Italian quick fix and start u off with they classic bread basket/w garlic butter spread that was tastyashell. #BakedEats✓.
Always enjoy coming here for the pasta with vodka sauce.
Scratch kitchen, great staff, good atmosphere a gem of a restaurant.

The food was ok. Me and a friend split 2 meals so we could taste multiple meals. We had a shrimp risotto and mahi mahi. The risotto was nothing but butter and cheese. A very very rich risotto.  I was not a fan. The mahi mahi was good however overcooked. The best thing on both plates was garlic mash potatoes
Lovely decor, friendly staff, lovely choice of menu, recommend the hummus.
A nice place for a sit down lunch without the added expense of wait service.  The dinning area is in a beautiful winter garden.  Good sandwiches. salads and pasta dishes.
Awesome venue
What a beautiful spot for a wedding reception

We had our wedding here and it was amazing! From start to finish, and even afterwards Fay went over the top with her service and the staff delivered on the day of the wedding. So happy we chose Pazzo's at 311 to host our wedding. The venue is beautiful and they really transform the place to everything my wife dreamed of. We did both our wedding and rehearsal dinner here and both night were magical. We wouldn't change a thing and cannot recommend Pazzo's enough.
The venue is amazing!

It's the basement "cafeteria" for the office building above it but that is really a misleading description.  While it might occupy that role in the building it is more a fancy Italian restaurant complete with a wait staff, full table service and linens.  The menu is excellent and yet it's really not that expensive at all.  I've always had a good experience there.  When I take job candidates out for lunch this is frequently where we go.  Never had a wait for a table either.
A great place for a business lunch in the West Loop. Pleasant atmosphere, friendly servers, delicious Italian food. Usually have really good lunch specials, like Shrimp Risotto, and great salads.

Second time here and my pasta dish was pretty bland. Definitely wouldn't get it again. Pasta had no flavor. Service was okay too. I had a better experience before with delicious food. Maybe chef has changed?  The express place is good and quick so would go there. For a nice sit down place, maybe try elsewhere if you aren't wanting pasta.
(Translated by Google) I recommend it very much.  (Original) Çok beğendim öneririm.

Nice spot for large group dinners and such, seems like their main line of business perhaps. Nice location with a fair amount of space and a nice environment. Catered food for my company's holiday party was good but not great. Bar selection is fair, and service was kind. Not hugely impressive, but if you're here it probably isn't to be impressed.

I noticed that the price was higher than I remembered after receiving my food and was told that prices had gone up and that the menus, or at least the one I was given, was incorrect. Bit of a bait and switch. They promptly removed the outdated pile of menus but made me pay the new price despite the menu I was given. That’s bad business.
Sit down area which is up scale fare. There is also an Express for take out. Nice public court for with tables for eating and bring your own lunch in the atrium.

I have only been here once, while visiting Chicago (seeing Coldplay), this place was AMAZING. I wish I could go back again soon. The service is so kind and generous, feels like home. Their salads are amazing! The portions are just right, unlike other restaurants that you may experience. The quiet atmosphere for small groups is amazing and so homey. You will love this place if you are trying to find somewhere new to explore in Chicago.
Very good. I like their southwestern salad for lunch. It's the perfect balance of salt and flavors; not too much dressing.
Good place. Good was very nice
Great place for a wedding though the lobby's not set up for good acoustics. Also, when attending a wedding, don't get the beef unless you like it well done

Pazzo's Express - I had lunch at Pazzo's Express  yesterday. I had the worst Caprese sandwich I gave ever had.  First, they used shredded lettuce which doesn't even belong on that sandwich.  Then, the description of the sandwich stated "thick slices of tomato" but they only used the thin slices they use for their other sandwiches.  There was barely any mozzarella cheese, probably about two ounces and no basil.  Basically what I got was a bread sandwich.  A complete failure.
Every Thursday is Buffalo day I love the buffalo chicken salad.
So good very small and local much go!
My favorite downtown Italian place!
Decent food at a decent price for Chicago.  Nice area to sit and eat and relax a little.
Great wedding venue. The natural lighting is the best thing about this space.
Good food , great service and reasonable prices! Mr.Lucky
Very good
Salads are good.  Service is slow.  The special is always a variation of risotto.
Good Italian food, friendly staff, and our order came out in perfect timing, and the location is awesome, highly recommend it
Great food and excellent service. I've been here probably 10 times and I've NEVER had anything bad.
Great food.  Nice atmosphere
food is good
Quiet place for lunch, if you eat inside.
Great food, great service, and great location!
Great venue.  Acoustics could be better tho.
gorgeous event space and delicious food
Love this place
I always feel like I'm at a home away from home here, the staff is extremely personable. Great place for a drink or three after work.
Always great food and service
Nice place to lunch.  Food is good.  Easy to have relaxing conversations with your companions.  The atrium is pretty but i recommend inside for the quiet atmosphere.
Beautiful place.

I had lunch with my daughter here yesterday and our service was absolutely horrible.  We were seated right away and the waitress was at the table within seconds with menus and taking our drink order.  She was back quickly to take our lunch order.  Then the hostess stopped by to make sure we were being waited on.  And that's where it ended. We waited a long time for our food, which by the way, was brought to our table by the hostess.  No one ever came back to the table after that.  No one asked how our meal was, if we wanted more drinks, bread, butter, nothing!!  We were completely ignored as if we were not even there.  All other customers had left by then (it was about 2pm) and it appeared the staff was setting up for a party.  After waiting patiently for someone to check on us, we ended up going into the kitchen to ask for left over containers and our check.  After waiting again, the bus boy finally brought them out to us.  We never did see our waitress until we were getting up to leave.  She hustled over to take our money.  When I asked her where she'd been/what happened, she said someone else was covering for her.  I've been to this location several times and never had such a bad experience. Unfortunately, the manger never came out to apologize or provide an explanation.  I would appreciate hearing back from someone with a good explanation as to what happened.  I hope my feedback can be used to make improvements so other customers don't get left behind sitting and waiting.
Still on the search for Kellywise!!! Hope they have grilled cheese!! And coca cola!! Take the Hurricanes out for the season!!!

Slight upscale Italian restaurant in the far SW corner of the loop.  Unless you know where this restaurant is already, you likely will not stumble onto it.  Located in 311 S Wacker building, in bottom of the atrium lobby, it provides an almost out feeling in atrium part of the restaurant.  Food was very good and selection was moderate.  Servers were well trained and the overall feel of the restaurant was leaning towards upscale.  At lunch, it was still possible to wear jeans and collared shirt.
Great food, both the restaurant and the express. Good service. Delicious specials.
Nice place with good views. The food is okay.
Great food big place nice music great service!!
Love the Mexicali salad
There is take-out and dine-in as well

We had our daughter's wedding there past weekend I couldn't tell you how nice this place is the Atrium is where we had her ceremony and later dinner by the waterfall, As far as the beautiful 80 Ft ceilings the architecture of the atrium is perfect for a such a setting! nevertheless The Catering manager Fay Sweeney is Wonderful, Well Sandy, Shylah and I walked in the place met Fay Sweeny and were very impressed with her personal attention we received through out our wedding preparations until the end on the wedding day and she was professional , attentive and courteous for all our needs until the end.  She is wonderful and does a great job of making this place very desirable. I highly recommend her and Pazzo's @311  The food was very good not typical wedding food we did have the best on the menu for our guest and its was impressive! servers were great and the bar was well attended as well. Fay's leadership and management style was impeccably impressive too.  I highly recommend this place ., by far the best experience ever !!! Fay & Staff keep up the good work.  Best Regards, Sandy & Jeff Abbas (Shylah's Wedding)
Good selection of pasta dishes. Friendly service.
This place is pretty good. I didn't think it was personally super great fantastic food.
Good food but not too expensive. Silverware could have been cleaner though.
This place is whatever. Got some scallops and calamari. It tasted alright.

Delicious homemade pasta. Large, open, comfortable atmosphere, you almost forget you're in the lobby of a large office building. Outstanding service. Pop music didn't really fit the vibe of the place, but since that's the worst complaint I can give them, they have my recommendation.
I go here every week to have my Signature Chicken Sandwich. I like the Ambience with nice Water falls. perfect place to visit with your Dear ones.

This is my 'go to' place for business lunches and meetings.  There is something on the menu for everyone.  The seating inside the restaurant is quiet if you are looking to hold a meeting and the seating near the fountain is very relaxing.  Also note that they have carryout service and their salads are freshly dressed as you like.
Amazing place, and reasonably priced too.

Had a nice lunch on a  Friday afternoon.  Grilled Tilapia served over grilled vegetables with a Balsamic drizzle. Sat in the Atrium with my date, a gorgeous lady, first date. I like this place and they had my favorite 18 year old Scotch at the bar. Will return soon.
